# Registering `{{ dist }}` in the FLEXT workspace

Created by `flext-infra codegen new --kind internal`. Workspace registration is
**never automatic** — it touches shared state and must be reviewed by the operator.

1. Add `{{ dist }}/` to the workspace members (root `pyproject.toml` → `[tool.uv.workspace].members`).
2. `make sync` from the workspace root to refresh `base.mk` and lazy exports.
3. `make check PROJECT={{ dist }}` and `make test PROJECT={{ dist }}`.
4. Commit with an explicit pathspec for `{{ dist }}/` and `projects/{{ dist }}.md`.

Until registered, the project builds standalone (the Makefile bootstraps `base.mk`).
